Pre-Game Insights: Pat Cummins believes the middle overs are the most crucial period in the 50-over format and currently an area where Australia is falling behind.
Australia's bowling strike rate during the middle overs has been the second-highest behind only the Netherlands in 2023.
Australia has lost the most wickets per innings between overs 11-40 in one-day internationals this year.

South Africa opener Quinton de Kock mentioned that the Proteas were contemplating bringing Tabraiz Shamsi into their lineup to face Australia due to similar surface conditions at Lucknow's Ekana Stadium.
Steve Smith emphasized the importance of extending partnerships and playing according to each surface given the differing conditions across the World Cup venues in India.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia's 2023 ODI World Cup fixtures include matches against South Africa on October 12, Sri Lanka on October 16, Pakistan on October 20, Netherlands on October 25, New Zealand on October 28, England on November 4, Afghanistan on November 7, and Bangladesh on November 11.
